parameters.name: CredentialConfig
parameters.description:
**If you do not have special requirements, leave this parameter empty.**

The authorization chain settings. For more information, see [Use authorization chains to access resources of other entities](~~465340~~).

parameters.name: ImageFormat
parameters.description: The encoding of the output image. By default, the output image uses the same encoding as the input image. Valid values: jpg, png, and webp.

parameters.name: Quality
parameters.description: The quality of the output image. This parameter applies only to JPG and WebP images. Valid values: 0 to 100. Default value: 80.

parameters.name: SourceURI
parameters.description:
The OSS URI of the input image.

Specify the OSS URI in the oss://${Bucket}/${Object} format, where `${Bucket}` is the name of the bucket in the same region as the current project and `${Object}` is the path of the object with the extension included.

Supported formats of input images include JPG, PNG, TIFF, JP2, and BMP.

parameters.name: TargetURI
parameters.description:
The OSS URI of the output image.

Specify the OSS URI in the oss://${Bucket}/${Object} format, where `${Bucket}` is the name of the bucket in the same region as the current project and `${Object}` is the path of the object with the extension included.

parameters.name: Targets
parameters.description: The bounding boxes and processing parameters.
